--- Test: Dictionary Operations & Methods ---
--- Basic Dictionary Operators ---
d1 + d2 (merge): {'a': 1, 'b': 20, 'c': 30}
d3 - 'b' (remove key): {'a': 1, 'c': 30}
d3 - 'nonexistent': {'a': 1, 'b': 20, 'c': 30}
--- Dictionary Methods ---
keys(): ['x', 'y', 'z']
values(): [100, 200, 300]
entries(): [['x', 100], ['y', 200], ['z', 300]]
--- get() method ---
get('x'): 100
get('missing', 999): 999
get('missing' no default): 0
--- has_key() / contains() ---
has_key('y'): 1
has_key('missing'): 0
--- pop() method ---
pop('z'): 300
dict after pop: {'x': 100, 'y': 200, 'z': 300}
pop('missing' with default): 555
--- pop_item() method ---
pop_item(): ['second', 2]
dict after pop_item: {'first': 1, 'second': 2}
--- update() method ---
after update: {'a': 1}
--- copy() and clear() ---
original after clear: {'a': 10}
copy is preserved: {'a': 10}
